        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3415108332" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7944970110501213704">Honestly, I had more fun thinking about me and my sisters forming an elite team of serial killers than I did reading this.<br/><br/>I will never understand books that have extremely fun-sounding plots and then are boring. It feels like this story spent more time on the main character&apos;s unrequited crush on a doctor (boring, sad) than it did on having a SISTER who KILLS all her BOYFRIENDS (rad, dreamy, exciting, and so on).<br/><br/>In other words this book sounded like my dream and turned into my nightmare.<br/><br/>Really it</span>
  <span id="freeText7944970110501213704" style="display:none">Honestly, I had more fun thinking about me and my sisters forming an elite team of serial killers than I did reading this.<br /><br />I will never understand books that have extremely fun-sounding plots and then are boring. It feels like this story spent more time on the main character's unrequited crush on a doctor (boring, sad) than it did on having a SISTER who KILLS all her BOYFRIENDS (rad, dreamy, exciting, and so on).<br /><br />In other words this book sounded like my dream and turned into my nightmare.<br /><br />Really it was just an unremarkable read for me. I won't remember much about these characters or this writing style or this narrative.<br /><br />Bottom line: The murder of my hopes and dreams at the hands of this book was the most consequential murder of all.<br /><br />---------------<br /><br />if she won't clean up the corpses of your sh*tty boyfriends, is she even your sister?<br /><br />review to come / 2.5 stars<br /><br />---<br /><br /><i>i am spending this month reading books by Black authors. please join me!</i><br /><br />book 1: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2953004100?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Stars and the Blackness Between Them</a><br />book 2: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372388250?type=review#rating_290994509" rel="nofollow noopener">Homegoing</a><br />book 3: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2718387154?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Let's Talk about Love</a><br />book 4: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3090142486?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Why I'm No Longer Talking to White People about Race</a><br />book 5: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3227618881?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Sellout</a><br />book 6: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372395187?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Queenie</a><br />book 7: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372400231?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Red at the Bone</a><br />book 8: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2586355320?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Weight of the Stars</a><br />book 9: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372396230?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">An American Marriage</a><br />book 10: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372415062?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Dear Ijeawaele</a><br />book 11: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3227620096?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Sing, Unburied, Sing</a><br />book 12: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3408947550?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Real Men Knit</a><br />book 13: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2997365269?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">All Boys Aren't Blue</a><br />book 14: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2192992500?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Piecing Me Together</a><br />book 15: My Sister, the Serial Killer</span>
