<div id="review_4077273927" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4077273927" />
    <a title="Gabby" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26560207-gabby"><img alt="Gabby" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1638230823p2/26560207.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4077273927?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabby" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabby" href="/user/show/26560207-gabby">Gabby</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=read-in-one-day">read-in-one-day</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=audiobooks-i-listened-to">audiobooks-i-listened-to</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=read-in-2021">read-in-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=3-star-books">3-star-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=thrillers-or-mystery">thrillers-or-mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=liked-it">liked-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26560207-gabby?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4077273927" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12138270297503916835"><b>Somewhere between a 3-3.5 stars</b><br/>There were some things I really enjoyed about this book and some things I didn’t enjoy as much. I love stories that follow sisters so I was super intrigued by a story that follows a girl dealing with her sister being a serial killer. <br/><br/>However, I feel like because it was the sister who was the serial killer, a lot of the ‘action’ of the book is written off the page… like we kind of just see the events after they’ve already happened. For that reason it didn’t feel sup</span>
  <span id="freeText12138270297503916835" style="display:none"><b>Somewhere between a 3-3.5 stars</b><br />There were some things I really enjoyed about this book and some things I didn’t enjoy as much. I love stories that follow sisters so I was super intrigued by a story that follows a girl dealing with her sister being a serial killer. <br /><br />However, I feel like because it was the sister who was the serial killer, a lot of the ‘action’ of the book is written off the page… like we kind of just see the events after they’ve already happened. For that reason it didn’t feel super thriller-like, it felt more like a family drama kind of story. Also a lot of the reviews are claiming this is dark humor, but I personally didn’t find anything humorous about the story? Maybe it just went over my head, but it was lost on me.<br /><br />But I really enjoyed the end of this book, and I appreciate how fast-paced this story was, (I’m a huge fan of short chapters like this haha) even though I do wish the story itself was a little longer so I could learn more about these characters.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12138270297503916835" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


